Family, political and government leaders attended the funeral of Frank Mdlalose. Courtesy #DStv403 NEWCASTLE - Former KwaZulu-Natal Premier, Dr Frank Mdlalose, was laid to rest on Thursday in Newcastle. He died of COVID-19 related complications on Saturday. A category two special funeral was held for him. READ: Tributes pour in for former KZN Premier Frank Mdlalose He served as the first democratic premier of KwaZulu-Natal and was later appointed as the country's ambassador to Egypt. eNCA's Thuba Vilane attended.